<span id="freeTextContainer12005456708076625351">I found this to be one of the more haunting Joseph Conrad stories; one that I can remember decades after my first reading. The story involves a sea captain who discovers a mysterious swimmer clinging to the side of the boat. Later we learn more about the swimmer&apos;s secret: the &quot;brand of Cain&quot; that he must bear. The swimmer becomes, in some way, the captain&apos;s double. A captivating story!</span>
  <span id="freeText12005456708076625351" style="display:none">I found this to be one of the more haunting Joseph Conrad stories; one that I can remember decades after my first reading. The story involves a sea captain who discovers a mysterious swimmer clinging to the side of the boat. Later we learn more about the swimmer's secret: the "brand of Cain" that he must bear. The swimmer becomes, in some way, the captain's double. A captivating story!</span>
